Virginia's Insurance Marketplace says that I am deceased though this is not correct, how do I correct this error?


Generally, a customer reported as deceased
because a credit bureau, a credit card company, a bank, or the Social Security Administration made a typo or had a computer glitch.
The error gets attached to your social security number and is reported to Virginia's Insurance Marketplace when we verify your information with the Social Security Administration.

If this is indeed an error, you can provide Virginia's Insurance Marketplace with copies of any one of the following documents to show this was done in error (DO NOT SEND ORIGINAL DOCUMENTS):


Passport;




Driver's license;




Employee ID card;




Military record;




School ID card, record or report card;




Marriage or divorce record;




Adoption record;




Health insurance card (except a Medicare card);




Certified copy of medical record;




Life insurance policy;




Court order for name change; or




Church membership that establishes your identity.



All documentation should be mailed to:

Virginia's Insurance Marketplace Customer Service

PO Box 428
Birmingham AL 35201

With a cover letter indicating what the documents are for.
